<paragraph blockId="17.[121,762,1620,1769]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2799">
<taxonomicName box="[121,389,1620,1644]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="17" pageNumber="2799" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="melliventris">
<emphasis box="[121,389,1620,1644]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2799">Lactobacillus melliventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows from 15 to 50 °C. Produce acid from glucose, fructose, mannose and gentiobiose, but not from galactose, ribose, sucrose, maltose and lactose [
<bibRefCitation author="Olofsson TC &amp; Alsterfjord M &amp; Nilson B &amp; Butler E &amp; Vasquez A." box="[719,750,1682,1706]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2799" pagination="3109 - 3119" refId="ref63118" refString="89. Olofsson TC, Alsterfjord M, Nilson B, Butler E, Vasquez A. Lactobacillus apinorum sp. nov., Lactobacillus mellifer sp. nov., Lactobacillus mellis sp. nov., Lactobacillus melliventris sp. nov., Lactobacillus kimbladii sp. nov., Lactobacillus helsingborgensis sp. nov. and Lactobacillus kullabergensis sp. nov., isolated from the honey stomach of the honeybee Apis mellifera. Int J Syst Evol Microbiol 2014; 64: 3109 - 3119." type="journal article" year="2014">89</bibRefCitation>
]. Thegenome size is 2.12 Mbp and the mol% G+C content of DNAis 35.9.
</paragraph>
